Poison!

1086
01:02:13,680 --> 01:02:15,600
You know, I did all my own stunts.

1087
01:02:21,420 --> 01:02:25,480
All of this came from my amazing fans in the Land of the Living.

1088
01:02:26,610 --> 01:02:29,400
They leave me more offerings than I know what to do with.

1089
01:02:30,630 --> 01:02:31,850
Hey, what's wrong?

1090
01:02:31,950 --> 01:02:33,850
Is it too much? You look overwhelmed.

1091
01:02:33,880 --> 01:02:36,220
N-no, It's all great.

1092
01:02:36,250 --> 01:02:38,560
- But? - It's just...

1093
01:02:38,740 --> 01:02:41,800
I've been looking up to you my whole life.

1094
01:02:41,910 --> 01:02:44,490
You're the guy who actually did it.

1095
01:02:45,940 --> 01:02:48,470
But did you ever regret it?

1096
01:02:48,500 --> 01:02:52,180
Choosing music over everything else?

1097
01:02:52,630 --> 01:02:57,090
It was hard saying goodbye to my hometown.

1098
01:02:57,120 --> 01:02:58,980
Heading off on my own.

1099
01:02:59,100 --> 01:03:01,280
Leaving your family?

1100
01:03:01,470 --> 01:03:02,870
Si.

1101
01:03:03,040 --> 01:03:06,050
But I could not have done it differently.

1102
01:03:06,320 --> 01:03:09,260
One cannot deny who one is meant to be.

1103
01:03:09,600 --> 01:03:11,950
And you, my great-great-grandson...

1104
01:03:11,980 --> 01:03:14,400
are meant to be a musician.

1105
01:03:16,330 --> 01:03:19,120
You and I, we are artists, Miguel.

1106
01:03:19,150 --> 01:03:21,320
We cannot belong to one family.

1107
01:03:21,350 --> 01:03:23,810
The world is our family!

1108
01:03:25,030 --> 01:03:27,660
Ooh-hoo! Ooh! The fireworks have begun!

1109
01:03:38,280 --> 01:03:42,220
Soon, the party will move across town for my sunrise spectacular.

1110
01:03:42,690 --> 01:03:45,450
Hunh! Miguel, you must come to the show!

1111
01:03:45,670 --> 01:03:47,640
You will be my guest of honor.

1112
01:03:47,660 --> 01:03:50,310
- You mean it? - Of course, my boy.

1113
01:03:52,380 --> 01:03:53,970
I can't.

1114
01:03:53,990 --> 01:03:56,480
I have to get home before sunrise.

1115
01:03:56,510 --> 01:03:59,090
Oy! I really do need to get you home.

1116
01:04:02,960 --> 01:04:05,360
It has been an honor.

1117
01:04:05,490 --> 01:04:07,960
I am sorry to see you go, Miguel.

1118
01:04:08,020 --> 01:04:10,130
I hope you die very soon.

1119
01:04:12,540 --> 01:04:14,210
You know what I mean.

1120
01:04:16,000 --> 01:04:17,560
Miguel...

1121
01:04:17,670 --> 01:04:19,420
I give you my blessing.

1122
01:04:19,440 --> 01:04:21,390
We had a deal, chamaco.

1123
01:04:21,410 --> 01:04:23,960
Who are you? What is the meaning of this?

1124
01:04:24,860 --> 01:04:27,740
Oh, Frida. I thought you couldn't make it.

1125
01:04:27,870 --> 01:04:29,670
You said you'd take back my photo.

1126
01:04:29,750 --> 01:04:31,340
You promised, Miguel.

1127
01:04:31,370 --> 01:04:33,050
You know this uh, man?

1128
01:04:33,180 --> 01:04:34,790
I just met him tonight.

1129
01:04:34,810 --> 01:04:36,820
He told me he knew you.

1130
01:04:37,280 --> 01:04:39,220
H...Hector?

1131
01:04:39,250 --> 01:04:40,630
Please, Miguel.

1132
01:04:40,650 --> 01:04:42,300
Put my photo up.

1133
01:04:44,000 --> 01:04:48,520
My friend. You're... you're being forgotten.

1134
01:04:48,540 --> 01:04:49,610
And whose fault is that?

1135
01:04:49,630 --> 01:04:51,650
- Hector, please. - Those were my songs you took.

1136
01:04:51,670 --> 01:04:53,300
My songs that made you famous.

1137
01:04:53,320 --> 01:04:55,250
- What? - If I'm being forgotten...

1138
01:04:55,280 --> 01:04:57,280
It's because you never told anyone that I wrote them.

1139
01:04:57,300 --> 01:05:00,620
That's crazy. De la Cruz wrote all his own songs.

1140
01:05:00,640 --> 01:05:02,290
You wanna tell him? Or should I?

1141
01:05:02,320 --> 01:05:04,910
Hector, I never meant to take credit.

1142
01:05:04,940 --> 01:05:07,330
We made a great team, but...

1143
01:05:07,350 --> 01:05:11,410
you died, and... I-I only sang your songs because

1144
01:05:11,440 --> 01:05:13,710
I wanted to keep a part of you alive.

1145
01:05:13,740 --> 01:05:15,450
Oh, how generous!

1146
01:05:15,470 --> 01:05:17,470
You really did play together.

1147
01:05:17,540 --> 01:05:20,110
Look, I don't want to fight about it.

1148
01:05:20,130 --> 01:05:22,020
I just want you to make it right.

1149
01:05:22,040 --> 01:05:24,040
Miguel can put my photo up.

1150
01:05:24,070 --> 01:05:26,290
- Hector. - And I can cross over the bridge.

1151
01:05:26,420 --> 01:05:28,050
I could see my girl.

1152
01:05:28,270 --> 01:05:29,670
Ernesto.

1153
01:05:30,080 --> 01:05:31,540
Remember the night I left?

1154
01:05:31,560 --> 01:05:32,960
That was a long time ago.

1155
01:05:32,980 --> 01:05:34,260
We drank together.

1156
01:05:34,290 --> 01:05:37,380
And you told me you would move heaven and earth for your amigo.

1157
01:05:37,620 --> 01:05:40,260
Well, I'm asking you to now.

1158
01:05:40,280 --> 01:05:42,050
Heaven and earth?

1159
01:05:42,080 --> 01:05:43,270
Like in the movie?

1160
01:05:43,300 --> 01:05:44,070
What?

1161
01:05:44,100 --> 01:05:45,760
That's Don Hidalgo's toast.

1162
01:05:45,790 --> 01:05:48,030
In the de la Cruz movie, "El Camino a Casa."

1163
01:05:48,050 --> 01:05:49,690
I'm talking about my real life, Miguel.

1164
01:05:49,720 --> 01:05:51,660
No, it's in there.

1165
01:05:51,710 --> 01:05:52,810
Look!

1166
01:05:53,250 --> 01:05:55,440
This calls for a toast.

1167
01:05:55,460 --> 01:05:57,100
To our friendship! Haha!

1168
01:05:57,130 --> 01:05:59,690
I would move heaven and earth for you, mi amigo.

1169
01:05:59,710 --> 01:06:02,600
But in the movie, Don Hidalgo poisons the drink.

1170
01:06:02,710 --> 01:06:04,390
Salud.

1171
01:06:04,410 --> 01:06:06,140
Poison!

1172
01:06:07,910 --> 01:06:09,910
That night, Ernesto.

1173
01:06:10,230 --> 01:06:12,030
The night I left.

1174
01:06:12,130 --> 01:06:14,640
We've been performing on the road for months.

1175
01:06:14,670 --> 01:06:17,870
I got homesick and I packed up my songs.

1176
01:06:18,190 --> 01:06:19,960
You wanna give up now?

1177
01:06:20,080 --> 01:06:22,130
When we're this close to reaching our dream?

1178
01:06:22,160 --> 01:06:24,150
This was your dream. You'll manage.

1179
01:06:24,180 --> 01:06:26,320
I can't do this without your songs, Hector.

1180
01:06:26,340 --> 01:06:27,900
I'm going home, Ernesto.

1181
01:06:27,930 --> 01:06:30,310
Hate me if you want. But my mind is made up.

1182
01:06:33,290 --> 01:06:35,610
Oh, I could never hate you.

1183
01:06:35,640 --> 01:06:40,060
If you must go, then I'm... I'm sending you off with a toast.

1184
01:06:43,020 --> 01:06:44,500
To our friendship.

1185
01:06:44,530 --> 01:06:47,630
I would move heaven and earth for you, mi amigo.

1186
01:06:47,660 --> 01:06:49,160
Salud!

1187
01:06:53,640 --> 01:06:55,500
You walked me to the train station.

1188
01:06:55,540 --> 01:06:58,050
But I felt a pain in my stomach.

1189
01:06:58,070 --> 01:07:00,240
I thought it must have been something I ate.

1190
01:07:00,260 --> 01:07:02,320
Perhaps it was that chorizo, my friend.

1191
01:07:02,340 --> 01:07:05,100
Or something I drank.

1192
01:07:08,590 --> 01:07:10,430
I woke up dead.

1193
01:07:11,760 --> 01:07:13,160
You...

1194
01:07:13,180 --> 01:07:14,770
poisoned me!

1195
01:07:14,790 --> 01:07:17,700
You're confusing movies with reality, Hector.

1196
01:07:17,890 --> 01:07:21,730
All this time, I thought it was just bad luck.

1197
01:07:22,090 --> 01:07:25,420
I never thought that you might have...

1198
01:07:25,440 --> 01:07:27,170
that you...

1199
01:07:30,160 --> 01:07:31,680
How could you?

1200
01:07:31,700 --> 01:07:32,460
Hector!

1201
01:07:32,490 --> 01:07:33,620
Security! Security!

1202
01:07:34,000 --> 01:07:36,630
You took everything away from me!

1203
01:07:37,560 --> 01:07:38,800
You rat!

1204
01:07:39,470 --> 01:07:41,110
Have him taken care of.

1205
01:07:41,140 --> 01:07:43,020
He's not well.

1206
01:07:43,040 --> 01:07:44,620
I just wanted to move back home!

1207
01:07:44,640 --> 01:07:47,230
No! No!

1208
01:07:48,860 --> 01:07:50,200
I apologize.

1209
01:07:50,810 --> 01:07:52,390
Where were we?

1210
01:07:52,610 --> 01:07:54,610
You were going to give me your blessing.

1211
01:07:54,640 --> 01:07:57,020
Yes... ah... Si.

1212
01:07:59,690 --> 01:08:01,320
Miguel...

1213
01:08:01,350 --> 01:08:04,700
My reputation... it is...

1214
01:08:04,730 --> 01:08:07,310
very important to me.

1215
01:08:07,340 --> 01:08:09,600
I would hate to have you think...

1216
01:08:09,620 --> 01:08:13,700
That you m-murdered Hector for his songs?

1217
01:08:14,840 --> 01:08:16,780
You don't think that.

1218
01:08:17,040 --> 01:08:18,180
Do you?

1219
01:08:18,280 --> 01:08:23,060
I... No... Everyone knows you're the... the good guy.

1220
01:08:29,020 --> 01:08:32,960
Papa Ernesto... my blessing?

1221
01:08:34,050 --> 01:08:35,850
Security?

1222
01:08:36,030 --> 01:08:39,070
Take care of Miguel. He'll be extending his stay.

1223
01:08:39,100 --> 01:08:40,490
What?

1224
01:08:40,510 --> 01:08:42,080
But I'm your family!

1225
01:08:42,110 --> 01:08:44,190
And Hector was my best friend.

1226
01:08:44,490 --> 01:08:47,740
Success doesn't come for free, Miguel.

1227
01:08:47,870 --> 01:08:51,390
You have to be willing to do whatever it takes to...

1228
01:08:51,410 --> 01:08:53,880
seize your moment.

1229
01:08:53,900 --> 01:08:56,080
I know you understand.

1230
01:08:56,100 --> 01:08:58,100
No! No!

1231
01:09:00,090 --> 01:09:01,540
Let go!

1232
01:09:01,950 --> 01:09:03,110
No!

1233
01:09:03,340 --> 01:09:04,800
Aah!

1234
01:09:25,260 --> 01:09:26,700
Help!

1235
01:09:27,180 --> 01:09:28,940
Can anyone hear me?

1236
01:09:29,730 --> 01:09:31,730
I wanna go home!

1237
01:09:48,090 --> 01:09:49,060
Huh?

1238
01:09:50,480 --> 01:09:51,810
H-Hector?

1239
01:09:51,840 --> 01:09:53,920
- Kid? - Oh, Hector!

1240
01:09:54,650 --> 01:09:55,920
You were right.

1241
01:09:55,940 --> 01:09:57,820
I should have gone back to my family.

1242
01:09:57,890 --> 01:10:00,940
- Hey, hey, hey. - They told me not to be like de la Cruz.

1243
01:10:01,000 --> 01:10:03,070
- But I didn't listen. - Hey, it's okay.

1244
01:10:03,100 --> 01:10:05,440
But I told them I didn't care if they remembered me.

1245
01:10:05,470 --> 01:10:08,520
I didn't care if was on the stupid ofrenda.

1246
01:10:08,620 --> 01:10:10,840
Hey, chamaco, it's okay.

1247
01:10:10,870 --> 01:10:12,090
It's okay.

1248
01:10:12,110 --> 01:10:14,520
I told them I didn't care.

1249
01:10:16,500 --> 01:10:19,240
- Huh! Oh! - Hector!

1250
01:10:19,260 --> 01:10:21,080
Hector?

1251
01:10:21,700 --> 01:10:23,570
She's...

1252
01:10:23,810 --> 01:10:25,530
forgetting me.

1253
01:10:25,560 --> 01:10:26,870
Who?

1254
01:10:27,240 --> 01:10:28,890
My daughter.

1255
01:10:30,720 --> 01:10:34,960
She's the reason you wanted to cross the bridge.

1256
01:10:35,460 --> 01:10:37,740
I just wanted to see her again.

1257
01:10:39,060 --> 01:10:41,330
I never should have left Santa Cecilia.

1258
01:10:42,420 --> 01:10:44,560
I wish I could apologize.

1259
01:10:44,580 --> 01:10:48,210
I wish I could tell her that her Papa was trying to come home.

1260
01:10:48,490 --> 01:10:51,180
That he loved her so much.

1261
01:10:53,390 --> 01:10:55,040
My Coco.

1262
01:10:57,720 --> 01:10:58,990
Coco?

1263
01:11:14,140 --> 01:11:15,440
Where?

1264
01:11:15,680 --> 01:11:17,860
Where did you get this?

1265
01:11:18,040 --> 01:11:20,390
That's my Mama Coco.

1266
01:11:20,410 --> 01:11:22,470
That's my Mama Imelda.

1267
01:11:22,810 --> 01:11:24,470
Is that...

1268
01:11:25,400 --> 01:11:26,590
You?

1269
01:11:30,070 --> 01:11:31,180
We're...

1270
01:11:32,150 --> 01:11:33,580
- family? - Family?

1271
01:11:46,030 --> 01:11:48,850
I always hoped I'd see her again.

1272
01:11:48,980 --> 01:11:50,690
That she'd miss me.

1273
01:11:50,770 --> 01:11:52,600
Maybe put up my photo.

1274
01:11:53,460 --> 01:11:54,950
But it never happened.

1275
01:11:56,080 --> 01:11:57,580
You know the worst part?

1276
01:11:57,890 --> 01:12:00,850
Even if I never got to see Coco in the living world...

1277
01:12:00,960 --> 01:12:03,680
I thought at least one day, I'd see her here.

1278
01:12:03,840 --> 01:12:06,330
Give her the biggest hug.

1279
01:12:07,850 --> 01:12:10,510
But she's the last person who remembers me.

1280
01:12:11,340 --> 01:12:13,560
The moment she's gone from the living world...

1281
01:12:13,740 --> 01:12:15,560
You disappear.

1282
01:12:15,580 --> 01:12:17,340
From this one.

1283
01:12:17,990 --> 01:12:19,670
You'll never get to see her.

1284
01:12:19,690 --> 01:12:21,360
Ever again.

1285
01:12:24,580 --> 01:12:25,700
You know...

1286
01:12:25,730 --> 01:12:27,630
I wrote her a song once.

1287
01:12:27,650 --> 01:12:30,030
We used to sing it every night.

1288
01:12:30,060 --> 01:12:31,540
At the same time.

1289
01:12:31,670 --> 01:12:34,370
No matter how far apart we were.

1290
01:12:35,480 --> 01:12:38,080
What I wouldn't give to sing it to her.

1291
01:12:38,120 --> 01:12:39,090
One...

1292
01:12:39,150 --> 01:12:40,110
last...

1293
01:12:40,200 --> 01:12:41,460
time.

1294
01:13:11,210 --> 01:13:12,460
Papa!

1295
01:13:47,820 --> 01:13:49,930
H-He stole your guitar.

1296
01:13:49,960 --> 01:13:51,880
He stole your songs.

1297
01:13:52,040 --> 01:13:54,530
You should be the one the world remembers.

1298
01:13:54,560 --> 01:13:55,780
Not de la Cruz.

1299
01:13:55,800 --> 01:13:58,230
I didn't write "Remember Me" for the world.

1300
01:13:58,420 --> 01:14:00,400
I wrote it for Coco.

1301
01:14:02,030 --> 01:14:04,740
I'm a pretty sorry excuse for a great-great-grandpa.

1302
01:14:04,770 --> 01:14:08,210
Are you kidding? A minute ago, I thought I was related to a murderer.

1303
01:14:08,240 --> 01:14:10,320
You're a total upgrade.

1304
01:14:10,660 --> 01:14:12,410
My whole life...

1305
01:14:12,430 --> 01:14:14,840
there's been something that made me different.

1306
01:14:14,890 --> 01:14:17,260
And I never knew where it came from.

1307
01:14:17,850 --> 01:14:19,170
But now, I know.

1308
01:14:19,200 --> 01:14:20,930
It comes from you!

1309
01:14:21,340 --> 01:14:23,360
I'm proud we're family.

1310
01:14:24,250 --> 01:14:26,690
I'm proud to be his family!

1311
01:14:33,860 --> 01:14:36,510
I'm proud to be his family!

1312
01:14:51,550 --> 01:14:52,740
Dante?

1313
01:14:54,400 --> 01:14:55,850
Dante!

1314
01:14:58,770 --> 01:15:00,200
It's Dante!

1315
01:15:05,290 --> 01:15:06,480
Haha!

1316
01:15:11,210 --> 01:15:12,770
Imelda!

1317
01:15:13,150 --> 01:15:14,770
Hector.

1318
01:15:15,090 --> 01:15:16,570
You look good.

1319
01:15:27,670 --> 01:15:28,930
Dante!

1320
01:15:28,960 --> 01:15:31,560
You knew he was my Papa Hector the whole time!

1321
01:15:31,590 --> 01:15:33,150
You are a real spirit guide.

1322
01:15:33,170 --> 01:15:36,150
Who's a good spirit guide? You are!

1323
01:15:55,580 --> 01:15:56,830
Dante!

1324
01:16:20,800 --> 01:16:22,160
There they are!

1325
01:16:22,190 --> 01:16:24,090
Miguelito! Miguelito!

1326
01:16:28,630 --> 01:16:30,410
Gracias, Dios mio!

1327
01:16:45,040 --> 01:16:46,960
Mijo, I was so worried.

1328
01:16:46,990 --> 01:16:49,320
Thank goodness we found you in time.

1329
01:16:50,070 --> 01:16:51,600
And you.

1330
01:16:51,620 --> 01:16:54,050
How many times must I turn you away?

1331
01:16:54,070 --> 01:16:55,080
Imelda...

1332
01:16:55,100 --> 01:16:58,590
I want nothing to do with you. Not in life, not in death.

1333
01:16:58,620 --> 01:17:02,330
I spent decades protecting my family from your mistakes.

1334
01:17:02,360 --> 01:17:05,710
He spends five minutes with you, and I have to fish him out of a sinkhole!

1335
01:17:05,740 --> 01:17:07,460
I wasn't in there 'cause of Hector.

1336
01:17:07,480 --> 01:17:09,460
He was in there 'cause of me.

1337
01:17:09,490 --> 01:17:12,140
He was just trying to get me home.

1338
01:17:12,160 --> 01:17:13,980
I didn't wanna listen.

1339
01:17:14,000 --> 01:17:15,920
But he was right.

1340
01:17:16,070 --> 01:17:18,650
Nothing is more important than family.

1341
01:17:20,070 --> 01:17:22,630
I'm ready to accept your blessing.

1342
01:17:22,660 --> 01:17:24,760
And your conditions.

1343
01:17:24,790 --> 01:17:27,440
But first, I need to find de la Cruz.

1344
01:17:27,460 --> 01:17:28,800
To get Hector's photo.

1345
01:17:28,830 --> 01:17:30,800
- What? - So he can see Coco again.

1346
01:17:30,820 --> 01:17:32,670
Hector should be on our ofrenda.

1347
01:17:32,690 --> 01:17:34,230
He's part of our family.

1348
01:17:34,260 --> 01:17:35,760
He left this family.

1349
01:17:35,790 --> 01:17:37,440
He tried to go home to you and Coco.

1350
01:17:37,460 --> 01:17:39,490
But de la Cruz murdered him.

1351
01:17:40,360 --> 01:17:42,140
It's true, Imelda.

1352
01:17:42,590 --> 01:17:44,350
And so what if it's true?

1353
01:17:44,370 --> 01:17:46,700
You leave me alone with a child to raise,

1354
01:17:46,720 --> 01:17:48,660
and I'm just supposed to forgive you?

1355
01:17:48,760 --> 01:17:50,040
Imelda, I...

1356
01:17:50,600 --> 01:17:52,060
Hector?

1357
01:17:52,090 --> 01:17:53,210
Hunh!

1358
01:17:54,940 --> 01:17:56,740
I'm running out of time.

1359
01:17:57,500 --> 01:17:58,900
It's Coco.

1360
01:17:59,490 --> 01:18:01,220
She's forgetting you.

1361
01:18:02,260 --> 01:18:04,500
You don't have to forgive him.

1362
01:18:04,680 --> 01:18:07,610
But we shouldn't forget him.

1363
01:18:10,010 --> 01:18:12,580
I wanted to forget you.

1364
01:18:13,140 --> 01:18:15,180
I wanted Coco to forget you too, but...

1365
01:18:15,210 --> 01:18:17,610
This is my fault.

1366
01:18:17,830 --> 01:18:19,630
Not yours.

1367
01:18:21,070 --> 01:18:22,950
I'm sorry, Imelda.

1368
01:18:27,060 --> 01:18:28,710
Miguel...

1369
01:18:28,800 --> 01:18:31,170
If we help you get his photo...

1370
01:18:31,220 --> 01:18:32,780
you will return home.

1371
01:18:32,800 --> 01:18:34,360
No more music.

1372
01:18:34,820 --> 01:18:37,900
Family comes first.

1373
01:18:39,850 --> 01:18:43,140
I... I can't forgive you.

1374
01:18:45,070 --> 01:18:47,200
But I will help you.

1375
01:18:48,560 --> 01:18:50,980
So how do we get to de la Cruz?

1376
01:18:52,250 --> 01:18:55,030
I might know a way.

1377
01:19:45,220 --> 01:19:46,570
Good luck, muchacho.

1378
01:19:46,600 --> 01:19:47,910
Gracias, Frida.

1379
01:19:52,630 --> 01:19:53,690
Ah!

1380
01:19:56,140 --> 01:19:57,220
Here, let me help you with...

1381
01:19:57,240 --> 01:19:58,410
Don't touch me.

1382
01:19:59,310 --> 01:20:00,540
Everyone clear on the plan?

1383
01:20:00,570 --> 01:20:01,910
Find Hector's photo.

1384
01:20:01,940 --> 01:20:02,850
Give it to Miguel.

1385
01:20:02,880 --> 01:20:03,880
Send Miguel home.

1386
01:20:03,910 --> 01:20:05,070
Got your petals?

1387
01:20:06,180 --> 01:20:08,280
Now, we just have to find de la Cruz.

1388
01:20:08,310 --> 01:20:09,610
- Yes? - Ah!

1389
01:20:10,520 --> 01:20:12,470
Don't I know you?

1390
01:20:13,430 --> 01:20:15,670
That's for murdering the love of my life!

1391
01:20:15,700 --> 01:20:18,080
- Who the? - She's talking about me.

1392
01:20:18,110 --> 01:20:19,580
I'm the love your your life?

1393
01:20:19,610 --> 01:20:21,250
I don't know, I'm still angry at you.

1394
01:20:21,290 --> 01:20:22,840
Hector? How did you...

1395
01:20:22,860 --> 01:20:25,050
And that's for trying to murder my grandson!

1396
01:20:25,070 --> 01:20:27,410
- Grandson? - She's talking about me.

1397
01:20:27,440 --> 01:20:28,730
You!

1398
01:20:28,850 --> 01:20:31,780
Wait. You're related to Hector?

1399
01:20:31,810 --> 01:20:33,230
The photo!

1400
01:20:34,830 --> 01:20:36,250
Eh...

1401
01:20:36,980 --> 01:20:38,340
After him!

1402
01:20:40,570 --> 01:20:42,130
Security, ayuda.

1403
01:20:42,880 --> 01:20:44,380
You said love of your life?

1404
01:20:44,400 --> 01:20:45,780
I don't know what I said.

1405
01:20:45,810 --> 01:20:47,510
That's what I heard.

1406
01:21:00,460 --> 01:21:02,460
Places, se?or. You're on in 30 seconds.

1407
01:21:10,150 --> 01:21:12,070
Miguel, I have it!

1408
01:21:20,620 --> 01:21:21,680
Oh!

1409
01:21:27,930 --> 01:21:29,020
Hurry, come on!

1410
01:21:31,400 --> 01:21:33,090
Ladies and gentleman!

1411
01:21:33,130 --> 01:21:39,120
The one. The only. Ernesto de la Cruz!

1412
01:21:48,180 --> 01:21:49,610
Get her off the stage!

1413
01:21:58,160 --> 01:21:59,260
Sing!

1414
01:21:59,680 --> 01:22:00,790
Sing!

1415
01:23:49,920 --> 01:23:52,300
I forgot what that felt like.

1416
01:23:52,650 --> 01:23:55,110
You... still got it.

1417
01:23:55,820 --> 01:23:57,630
Uh-h-hum...

1418
01:23:57,650 --> 01:23:59,180
Oh!

1419
01:24:00,670 --> 01:24:04,040
Miguel, I give you my blessing...

1420
01:24:04,860 --> 01:24:06,840
To go home...

1421
01:24:06,860 --> 01:24:09,550
To put up our photos...

1422
01:24:09,570 --> 01:24:11,380
And to never...

1423
01:24:11,410 --> 01:24:13,600
Never play music again.

1424
01:24:14,170 --> 01:24:19,350
To never forget how much your family loves you.

1425
01:24:21,690 --> 01:24:23,410
You're going home.

1426
01:24:27,070 --> 01:24:28,780
You're not going anywhere!

1427
01:24:30,230 --> 01:24:31,600
Imelda!

1428
01:24:31,670 --> 01:24:33,330
Stay back! Stay back!

1429
01:24:33,350 --> 01:24:35,470
All of you, stay back!

1430
01:24:35,500 --> 01:24:37,270
Not one more step.

1431
01:24:38,940 --> 01:24:40,250
Dante!

1432
01:24:41,910 --> 01:24:43,600
Ernesto, stop!

1433
01:24:44,570 --> 01:24:46,200
Leave the boy alone.

1434
01:24:46,220 --> 01:24:48,120
I've worked too hard, Hector.

1435
01:24:48,150 --> 01:24:50,340
Too hard to let him destroy everything.

1436
01:24:50,370 --> 01:24:52,270
He's a living child, Ernesto.

1437
01:24:52,290 --> 01:24:53,980
He's a threat.

1438
01:24:54,090 --> 01:24:58,260
You think I'd let him go back to the Land of the Living with your photo?

1439
01:24:58,290 --> 01:25:00,120
To keep your memory alive?

1440
01:25:00,150 --> 01:25:01,760
- No. - You're a coward!

1441
01:25:01,790 --> 01:25:05,430
I am Ernesto de la Cruz. The greatest musician of all time.

1442
01:25:05,450 --> 01:25:07,440
Hector's the real musician.

1443
01:25:07,470 --> 01:25:10,300
You're just the guy who murdered him and stole his songs.

1444
01:25:10,320 --> 01:25:11,550
Murdered?

1445
01:25:11,570 --> 01:25:14,050
I am the one who's willing to do what it takes

1446
01:25:14,080 --> 01:25:16,080
to seize my moment.

1447
01:25:16,100 --> 01:25:18,110
Whatever it takes.

1448
01:25:18,270 --> 01:25:20,060
Aah! Aah!

1449
01:25:20,140 --> 01:25:21,480
No!

1450
01:25:22,980 --> 01:25:24,800
- Miguel! - Miguel!

1451
01:25:25,280 --> 01:25:28,720
Apologies, old friend. But the show must go on.

1452
01:26:04,300 --> 01:26:05,940
Haha!

1453
01:26:06,130 --> 01:26:08,140
Boo! Boo!

1454
01:26:08,390 --> 01:26:10,520
Boo!

1455
01:26:10,810 --> 01:26:13,850
Hahaha! Please, please, mi familia!

1456
01:26:13,870 --> 01:26:15,240
- Murderer! - Get off the stage!

1457
01:26:15,260 --> 01:26:18,260
Orchestra, a-one, a-two, a-one...

1458
01:26:23,840 --> 01:26:25,550
Hey, creep!

1459
01:26:26,550 --> 01:26:27,820
Look!

1460
01:26:48,000 --> 01:26:49,190
Nice kitty.

1461
01:26:51,180 --> 01:26:52,210
Ah!

1462
01:26:53,330 --> 01:26:54,810
Put me down!

1463
01:26:54,830 --> 01:26:55,870
Please!

1464
01:26:55,900 --> 01:26:57,570
I'm begging you! Stop, stop!

1465
01:26:58,240 --> 01:26:59,460
Aaah!

1466
01:27:01,500 --> 01:27:03,310
Aah! Aaah!

1467
01:27:04,630 --> 01:27:06,820
Oooh!

1468
01:27:07,080 --> 01:27:08,640
Oh! No!

1469
01:27:08,700 --> 01:27:09,760
Aaah!

1470
01:27:11,920 --> 01:27:12,860
Hunh!

1471
01:27:20,090 --> 01:27:21,550
What did I miss?

1472
01:27:21,580 --> 01:27:23,260
Good boy, Dante.

1473
01:27:23,290 --> 01:27:24,710
Miguel!

1474
01:27:24,850 --> 01:27:26,190
Oh!

1475
01:27:26,210 --> 01:27:27,690
Hector!

1476
01:27:28,320 --> 01:27:30,050
The photo, I lost it.

1477
01:27:30,120 --> 01:27:31,810
It's okay, mijo.

1478
01:27:31,870 --> 01:27:33,190
It's...

1479
01:27:33,220 --> 01:27:34,870
Hector!

1480
01:27:35,150 --> 01:27:36,610
Hector?

1481
01:27:37,140 --> 01:27:38,490
Coco.

1482
01:27:38,700 --> 01:27:40,470
No, we can still find the photo.

1483
01:27:40,500 --> 01:27:42,710
Miguel, it's almost sunrise.

1484
01:27:42,960 --> 01:27:45,300
No, no, no. I can't leave you.

1485
01:27:45,320 --> 01:27:47,440
I promised I put your photo up.

1486
01:27:47,470 --> 01:27:49,740
I promised you'd see Coco.

1487
01:27:50,070 --> 01:27:52,290
We're both out of time, mijo.

1488
01:27:53,250 --> 01:27:55,120
No! No!

1489
01:27:55,150 --> 01:27:57,020
She can't forget you.

1490
01:27:57,040 --> 01:27:59,180
I just wanted her to know...

1491
01:27:59,450 --> 01:28:01,290
that I loved her.

1492
01:28:01,530 --> 01:28:02,930
Hector!

1493
01:28:03,030 --> 01:28:05,390
You have our blessing, Miguel.

1494
01:28:05,640 --> 01:28:08,010
No conditions.

1495
01:28:08,190 --> 01:28:11,000
No, Papa Hector. Please!

1496
01:28:14,920 --> 01:28:16,130
No.

1497
01:28:17,420 --> 01:28:18,650
Go home.

1498
01:28:18,680 --> 01:28:21,760
I promise! I-I won't let Coco forget you!

1499
01:28:49,300 --> 01:28:50,460
There he is!

1500
01:28:51,380 --> 01:28:53,270
Miguel! Stop!

1501
01:28:58,390 --> 01:28:59,590
Where have you been?

1502
01:28:59,610 --> 01:29:01,730
Ah! I need to see Mama Coco, please!

1503
01:29:01,760 --> 01:29:03,510
Huh! What are you doing with that?

1504
01:29:03,540 --> 01:29:04,630
Give it to me!

1505
01:29:04,660 --> 01:29:06,240
Miguel, stop.

1506
01:29:06,270 --> 01:29:08,760
Miguel! Miguel?

1507
01:29:08,780 --> 01:29:10,270
Miguel!

1508
01:29:10,630 --> 01:29:11,970
Mama Coco?

1509
01:29:11,990 --> 01:29:13,260
Can you hear me?

1510
01:29:13,280 --> 01:29:14,680
It's Miguel.

1511
01:29:14,950 --> 01:29:16,700
I-I saw your Papa!

1512
01:29:16,730 --> 01:29:19,240
Remember? Papa?

1513
01:29:19,610 --> 01:29:21,140
Please.

1514
01:29:21,280 --> 01:29:22,940
If you forget him.

1515
01:29:22,960 --> 01:29:24,450
He'll be gone.

1516
01:29:24,490 --> 01:29:25,970
Forever.

1517
01:29:27,240 --> 01:29:30,360
Here. This was his guitar, right?

1518
01:29:30,380 --> 01:29:32,460
He used to play it to you?

1519
01:29:34,540 --> 01:29:36,550
See, there he is.

1520
01:29:37,680 --> 01:29:41,200
Papa, remember? Papa?

1521
01:29:44,080 --> 01:29:45,170
Miguel!

1522
01:29:45,200 --> 01:29:48,360
Mama Coco, please. Don't forget him.

1523
01:29:53,700 --> 01:29:56,810
What are you doing to that poor woman?

1524
01:29:56,830 --> 01:29:57,920
It's okay, mother.

1525
01:29:57,940 --> 01:29:59,240
What's gotten into you?

1526
01:30:05,670 --> 01:30:07,620
I thought I lost you, Miguel.

1527
01:30:07,640 --> 01:30:09,320
I'm sorry, Papa.

1528
01:30:09,340 --> 01:30:10,940
We're all together now.

1529
01:30:10,960 --> 01:30:13,040
That's what matters.

1530
01:30:13,060 --> 01:30:14,660
Not all of us.

1531
01:30:14,680 --> 01:30:16,580
It's okay, Mamita.

1532
01:30:16,610 --> 01:30:20,570
Miguel, you apologize to your Mama Coco.

1533
01:30:23,420 --> 01:30:24,840
Mama Coco...

1534
01:30:29,970 --> 01:30:31,970
Well, apologize.

1535
01:30:35,840 --> 01:30:37,350
Mama Coco...

1536
01:30:37,540 --> 01:30:39,410
Your Papa...

1537
01:30:39,440 --> 01:30:41,880
He wanted you to have this.

1538
01:30:43,130 --> 01:30:45,180
Mama... wait...

1539
01:31:55,250 --> 01:31:57,330
Elena?

1540
01:31:57,350 --> 01:31:59,740
What's wrong, mija?

1541
01:31:59,910 --> 01:32:01,860
Nothing, Mama.

1542
01:32:02,010 --> 01:32:04,300
Nothing at all.

1543
01:32:04,920 --> 01:32:09,170
My Papa used to sing me that song.

1544
01:32:09,220 --> 01:32:11,740
He loved you, Mama Coco.

1545
01:32:11,880 --> 01:32:16,110
Your Papa loved you so much.

1546
01:32:34,270 --> 01:32:37,940
I kept his letters.

1547
01:32:37,970 --> 01:32:40,950
Poems he wrote me.

1548
01:32:41,640 --> 01:32:43,470
And...

1549
01:33:01,830 --> 01:33:04,950
Papa was a musician.

1550
01:33:05,100 --> 01:33:07,480
When I was a little girl...

1551
01:33:07,510 --> 01:33:13,190
He and Mama would sing such beautiful songs.

1552
01:33:19,520 --> 01:33:22,070
One year later

1553
01:33:22,350 --> 01:33:24,190
Remember me

1554
01:33:24,220 --> 01:33:25,470
Forgotten.

1555
01:33:25,500 --> 01:33:27,080
And right over here,

1556
01:33:27,110 --> 01:33:29,780
one of Santa Cecilia's greatest treasures.

1557
01:33:29,800 --> 01:33:33,560
The home of the esteemed songwriter, Hector Rivera.

1558
01:33:33,590 --> 01:33:36,980
The letters Hector wrote home for his daughter, Coco

1559
01:33:37,000 --> 01:33:39,900
contain the lyrics for all of your favorite songs.

1560
01:33:39,930 --> 01:33:41,910
Not just "Remember Me."

1561
01:33:45,040 --> 01:33:47,570
And that man is your Papa Julio.

1562
01:33:47,600 --> 01:33:49,590
And there's Tia Rosita.

1563
01:33:49,620 --> 01:33:51,460
And your Tia Victoria.

1564
01:33:51,490 --> 01:33:54,230
And those two are Oscar and Felipe.

1565
01:33:54,390 --> 01:33:56,930
There aren't just old pictures, they're our family.

1566
01:33:56,950 --> 01:33:59,670
And they're counting on us to remember them.

1567
01:34:25,820 --> 01:34:28,490
Enjoy your visit, Hector.

1568
01:34:36,550 --> 01:34:37,720
Papa!

1569
01:34:37,740 --> 01:34:39,230
Coco!
